# Split-agent Canvas access — the ONLY file holding the Canvas credential.
#
# Copy to `.env.canvas` at your course-repo root and fill in the token.
#
# Read exclusively by lib/tools/canvas_run.py. In split-agent mode the token is
# deliberately NOT in `.env`, so that an agent denied read access to THIS file
# cannot authenticate to Canvas — it has no credential, and Canvas answers 401.
# That is what makes the block structural rather than advisory.
#
# ⚠️  Gitignore this file, and verify the rule bites BEFORE you write the secret:
#
#       git check-ignore -v .env.canvas
#
#     If that prints nothing, STOP — your token is one `git add -A` from being
#     committed. Also ignore `.env.backup*` if you keep a rollback copy of .env.
#
# See docs/split-agent-access.md.

CANVAS_API_TOKEN=
